Asplenium oblongifolium is a type of fern belonging to the family Aspleniaceae. 
It is a medium-sized fern with dark green, oblong-shaped fronds. 
The fronds are smooth to the touch and have a glossy finish. 
The leaflets are attached to the stem alternately and are about 10-20 cm long. 
This fern is commonly found in shady and damp areas such as tropical rainforests and wetlands. 
It is also used as an ornamental plant in gardens and indoor spaces. 
Asplenium oblongifolium is known for its ability to remove pollutants from the air, making it a popular choice for indoor air purification.
